# Dolibarr language file - Source file is en_US - pridge
# Language file for the Pridge Dolibarr Endpoint module.
PridgeDesc=Send receipt tickets to an external print collector over HTTPS
PridgeDescLong=Pridge Dolibarr Endpoint adds an HTTP transport to Dolibarr's built-in Receipt Printers module and TakePOS, without patching core or disabling that module. It registers a pridge:// stream wrapper so a printer configured with connector type "Local Printer" (Setup > Receipt Printers) forwards its ticket as a job to a PrintBridge Server, instead of writing to a local file. Add your server(s) below, then create a profile picking which server and endpoint token to use, and reference it from that module's printer setup - or use the "Adopt an existing printer" section to wire one up automatically.
PridgeDefaults=Default settings
PridgeDefaultsHelp=Used whenever a profile leaves the matching field blank. A default server (with a default endpoint token) is the normal setup; the fallback endpoint URL only matters when no server resolves at all (profile or default) - e.g. for the bundled test receiver.
PridgeServers=Pridge servers
PridgeServersHelp=A server is a PrintBridge Server instance's base URL (e.g. https://pridge.example.com). Profiles pick which server to submit print jobs to; the plugin API path (<base URL>/api/plugin/jobs) is added automatically.
PridgeProfiles=Pridge profiles
